HEADWORD: Ponent
<hw>Po"nent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF., fr. It.
<ets>ponente</ets>, properly, setting (applied to the setting sun), fr.
L. <ets>ponens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>ponere</ets> to set, put.]</ety>
<def>Western; occidental.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Forth rush the levant and the <qex>ponent</qex> winds.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pongee</ent>⟦br⟧
